## Widget deliverables by stage

| Stage | Widget epic | Focus |
|-------|-------------|--------|
| 0 | #1 | Governance, rules, intent |
| 1 | #7 | Rebrand, Apache 2.0, logo in navbar |
| 3 | #13 | Maps tab — D3 force graph, connection widget, filters |
| 4 | #32 | Tests tab — module/route test UI |

Stages 2 and backend-only work have **no widget epic**.

## UI shell (stage 3+)

Navbar tabs: **Enrichments** (default), **Composer**, **Maps**, **Logs**, **Tests**.  
Only **Maps** and **Tests** are implemented in stages 3–4; others remain **empty placeholder pages**.

## Out of scope (stages 0–4)

Stages 5–8 UI (investigation workspace, quarantine tooling, favourites runner).

## Stage 4 Tests behaviour (backend contract)

- Module list comes from `/api/v1/tests/*` — **excludes** `service_state: error` (8 upstream-broken modules).
- **Positive pass:** produced nuggets. **Negative pass:** `module_execution.verdict === 'clean_miss'` (not zero output alone).
- Show fixture icon from `fixture_kind` / `fixture_category` (positive vs negative).
- Backend guide: `@spiderfeet/.docs/analysis/stage4_seed_corpus_and_tests.md`

## Execution

1. Bind to SPEC-002 R2-03-03 / R2-04-04 / R2-04-08 when implementing UI stories
2. Branch `feature/<issue>-<slug>`; PR to `develop`
3. Exploratory review on Maps (#SFW-03-18) and Tests (#SFW-04-09) per GOV-08
